26:56.082 --> 26:58.918
PAGE: For nearly half a century,
San Francisco

26:58.951 --> 27:01.187
has been the capital
of queer activism

27:01.220 --> 27:03.089
in the United States.

27:03.122 --> 27:06.092
It was once a refuge
for World War II soldiers

27:06.125 --> 27:09.395
who were dishonorably discharged
for their sexuality.

27:09.428 --> 27:12.364
Then, as the gay populations
in the Castro

27:12.398 --> 27:15.902
and the Haight grew,
so did their political power.

27:15.935 --> 27:19.906
And in 1977, Harvey Milk
became the nation's first

27:19.939 --> 27:22.041
openly gay elected official

27:22.074 --> 27:25.745
and passed strict gay rights
protections citywide.

27:25.778 --> 27:27.980
MILK: There is no law
that says two human beings

27:28.014 --> 27:29.749
cannot love one another.

27:29.782 --> 27:32.985
PAGE: His murder the next year
left the city in agony

27:33.019 --> 27:35.154
but inspired tens of thousands

27:35.187 --> 27:36.923
to take to the streets
in mourning

27:36.956 --> 27:38.758
and continue his fight.

27:41.928 --> 27:45.464
However, today, violence
directed at the queer community

27:45.497 --> 27:47.834
is still a nationwide problem.

27:47.867 --> 27:51.904
And transgender women of color
face the most brutality,

27:51.938 --> 27:56.909
with an average life expectancy
of only 35 years.

27:56.943 --> 28:01.380
This is one of the biggest civil
rights issues of our generation.

28:01.413 --> 28:03.716
WOMAN: I am disappointed
in my community,

28:03.750 --> 28:05.451
as a queer black woman,

28:05.484 --> 28:07.787
with the nonresponse

28:07.820 --> 28:11.290
to our black trans sisters
being murdered out here.

28:11.323 --> 28:13.459
[ Cheering and applause ]

28:13.492 --> 28:15.828
PAGE: We are lucky enough
to meet with

28:15.862 --> 28:17.163
