49:03.308 --> 49:06.111
It's a city known
for its wealth and glamour.

49:06.144 --> 49:09.247
But it also has the largest
chronically homeless population

49:09.280 --> 49:11.116
in the country.

49:11.149 --> 49:16.321
And of the homeless youth,
40 percent are LGBTQ-identified.

49:16.354 --> 49:18.489
The Los Angeles LGBT Center

49:18.523 --> 49:20.325
is the world's
largest provider

49:20.358 --> 49:22.193
of programs and services

49:22.227 --> 49:24.329
dedicated to the queer community

49:24.362 --> 49:25.730
and has been leading the charge

49:25.763 --> 49:29.567
in helping LGBTQ youth
get off the streets.

49:29.600 --> 49:31.502
You know, L.A. sort of
has the dubious distinction

49:31.536 --> 49:33.638
of being the homeless youth
capital of the country.

49:33.671 --> 49:35.273
And there's a couple reasons
for that.

49:35.306 --> 49:37.742
One is the weather here
is better than, you know,

49:37.775 --> 49:39.377
any place where it snows.
Mm-hmm.

49:39.410 --> 49:41.046
And the other is that there's
sort of these ideas

49:41.079 --> 49:42.647
that kids are gonna come here
and be discovered and sort

49:42.680 --> 49:45.516
of the Hollywood glamour,
which is obviously not the case

49:45.550 --> 49:47.085
for most of our clients.

49:47.118 --> 49:48.686
So oftentimes, what will happen:

49:48.719 --> 49:51.356
These kids will get off the bus
with everything they own,

49:51.389 --> 49:53.191
typically in backpack.

49:53.224 --> 49:55.426
And within that first week,
they are likely to be beaten,

49:55.460 --> 49:57.262
robbed of
all of their possessions.

49:57.295 --> 49:59.430
They are likely to have done
drugs for the very first time.

49:59.464 --> 50:01.266
And they are likely to have
performed their first act

50:01.299 --> 50:02.767
of survival sex,
which is typically

50:02.800 --> 50:05.203
not for money, even.

50:05.236 --> 50:07.772
It's for food
or for a place to stay.

50:07.805 --> 50:10.641
To give you sort of a sense
of the scale of the problem,

50:10.675 --> 50:12.810
there are about 200 beds
in L.A. County

50:12.843 --> 50:16.114
that are specifically funded
for youth in general.

50:16.147 --> 50:17.648
Mm-hmm.
